# .cursorrules — DataNarasi Project
# Dibaca otomatis oleh Cursor IDE untuk semua file di project ini

You are an expert full-stack developer working on DataNarasi, an AI-powered
data analysis web application. Always read PROMPT.md first for full context.

## Project Context
- Laravel 12 backend + Python FastAPI microservice
- Vue 3 (Composition API only) + Inertia.js frontend
- Multi-AI narrative generation: Gemini → Kimi → GLM → NVIDIA NIM → MiniMax → Claude (fallback chain)
- Target users: Indonesian SMBs and data analysts
- All AI output must be in Bahasa Indonesia

## Code Style Rules

### PHP / Laravel
- PHP 8.2+ syntax always (readonly, enums, match, named args, fibers if needed)
- PSR-12 formatting
- Docblocks on every class and public method
- Return types mandatory on all functions
- Use Laravel helpers: collect(), now(), str(), filled(), blank()
- Repositories are NOT used — use Eloquent directly in Services
- Services are plain PHP classes in app/Services/, injected via constructor
- No facades inside Service classes — use dependency injection
- Exception handling: use Laravel's Handler, not try-catch in controllers

### Vue 3
- <script setup lang="ts"> always — TypeScript preferred but not mandatory
- defineProps() and defineEmits() always typed
- No direct DOM manipulation — use template refs only
- Composables go in resources/js/composables/
- No inline styles — Tailwind classes only
- Component names: PascalCase files, kebab-case in templates
- Emit events in kebab-case: emit('update-status')

### Python
- Type hints on every function parameter and return value
- Docstrings in every class and function (Indonesian description ok)
- Pandas: always handle FileNotFoundError, EmptyDataError, ParserError
- FastAPI: Pydantic models for all request/response bodies
- No global mutable state — pass config via function arguments

### SQL / Migrations
- Always use bigIncrements() for PKs
- Always add timestamps() to every table
- Foreign keys use constrained() with cascadeOnDelete() where appropriate
- Index columns used in WHERE clauses

## File Naming Conventions
- Laravel Controllers: PascalCase + Controller suffix (UploadController.php)
- Laravel Models: PascalCase singular (Report.php, not Reports.php)
- Laravel Jobs: PascalCase + Job suffix (ProcessDataJob.php)
- Vue Components: PascalCase (UploadZone.vue)
- Vue Pages: PascalCase in folder matching route (Pages/Report/Show.vue)
- Python modules: snake_case (ai_provider.py, prompt_builder.py)

## API Design
- All API routes under /api/v1/
- JSON responses always: { "success": bool, "data": any, "message": string }
- HTTP status codes used correctly (200, 201, 422, 500)
- Report webhook from Python to Laravel: POST /api/v1/reports/{id}/callback

## Security Rules
- Validate all file uploads: mime type, size, extension whitelist
- Never expose AI API keys in responses or logs
- Sanitize all user inputs before passing to Python service
- Use Laravel's storage disk abstraction — never direct file paths in DB

## When Writing Code
1. Show the full file path as a comment on the first line
2. Write concise Indonesian comments for logic blocks
3. After any migration, show the php artisan migrate command
4. After any new route, show it in route:list format
5. For Python files, always include the pip install command for new packages
